What is Route 53 ?
------------------
-53 is a DNS port Number
-Highly available and scalable DNS(Domain Name System) and domain management service
-It is used to route users request to applications hosted on AWS (www.aklr.shop)
-Route 53 maps domain names (like www.aklr.shop to IP addresses (192.168.1.1) so browsers can find your website 


Core Functions:
	-DNS service: Converts domain names to IP addresses (DNS resolutions)
	-Domain Registration: you can buy domains directly in Route 53
	-Highly available and Global
	
Use case: Hosting website in s3 + Cloudfront + Route 53 

what is TLS Certificate?
------------------------
-TLS : transport layer security used to enable HTTPS communication between clients and your application

Purpose:
--------
-Converts HTTP to HTTPS
-Secures commuication
-Protects sensitive data like passwords, card details etc


How TLS certificate works:
---------------------------
-Browser requests https://aklr.shop that server sends TLS certificate to browser
